  "instructions": [
    "Preheat grill to medium-high heat (375°F/190°C).",
    "Rinse the duck legs and pat them dry with paper towels.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together the tomato paste, garlic, Brazilian chili flakes, cumin, coriander, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Brush the duck legs with olive oil and sprinkle with the spice mixture.",
    "Place the duck legs on the grill and cook for 5 minutes on each side.",
    "Transfer the duck legs to a baking sheet and brush with red wine vinegar and lime juice.",
    "Return the duck legs to the grill and cook for an additional 5 minutes on each side.",
    "Garnish with fresh oregano and cilantro.",
    "Let the duck legs rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
  ],
